fixmath
------------------------------------------
Fixmath is a library of fixed-point math operations and functions. It is
designed to be portable, flexible and fast on platforms without floating-point
support:
 * The library is written in ANSI-C (C89).
 * The library is thread-safe.
 * There is no hard-coded fixed-point format. The user can set the binary
   point freely on a per-operation basis.
 * Simple arithmetic operations are inlined.
 * Performance is favoured over last-bit precision.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libfixmath-devel-1.4-1bl1
  libfixmath0-1.4-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.nongnu.org/fixmath/

Canonical download:
  mirror://savannah/fixmath/fixmath-1.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fixmath-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fixmath-1.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fixmath-1.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fixmath-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfixmath0-1.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfixmath-devel-1.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

